name: ProgressUserInfoKey
desc: Keys for the user info dictionary that affect the autogenerated localized additional description string.

items.name: init(String)
items.desc: Creates a new key using the specified string.

items.name: init(rawValue: String)
items.desc: Creates a new key using the raw value of a string you specify.

items.name: static let estimatedTimeRemainingKey: ProgressUserInfoKey
items.desc: A key with a corresponding value that represents the time remaining, in seconds.

items.name: static let throughputKey: ProgressUserInfoKey
items.desc: A key with a corresponding value that indicates the speed of data processing, in bytes per second.

items.name: static let fileAnimationImageKey: ProgressUserInfoKey
items.desc: A key with a corresponding value that is an image, typically an icon to represent the file.

items.name: static let fileAnimationImageOriginalRectKey: ProgressUserInfoKey
items.desc: A key with a corresponding value that indicates the starting location of the image onscreen.

items.name: static let fileCompletedCountKey: ProgressUserInfoKey
items.desc: A key with a corresponding value that represents the number of completed files.

items.name: static let fileIconKey: ProgressUserInfoKey
items.desc: A key with a corresponding value that must be an image, typically an icon to represent the file.

items.name: static let fileOperationKindKey: ProgressUserInfoKey
items.desc: A key with a corresponding value that indicates the kind of file operation a progress object represents.

items.name: static let fileTotalCountKey: ProgressUserInfoKey
items.desc: A key with a corresponding value that represents the total number of files within a file operation.

items.name: static let fileURLKey: ProgressUserInfoKey
items.desc: A key with a corresponding value that represents the file URL of a file operation for the progress object.
